<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE COVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the vernacular of '40s prison flicks, one of history's most infamous 
gangsters goes to the big house in "The Revenge of Al Capone," a new NBC movie 
airing Sunday at 9 p.m. on Channels 4, 36 and 39. 
</P>
<P>
Ray Sharkey, who made his mark on "Wiseguy" as manipulative Sonny Steelgrave, 
portrays the cigar-smoking king of Chicago's underworld. Keith Carradine plays 
FBI agent Michael Rourke, who gets him for tax evasion. 
</P>
<P>
Written by Tracy Keenan Wynn ("Tribes," "The Autobiography of Miss Jane 
Pittman"), the film focuses on Capone's efforts to run his empire from Cook 
County Jail, where he vows vengeance against Rourke. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, Keith Carradine and Ray Sharkey Steve Fontanini / Los Angeles 
Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
