<P>
APARTMENTS GET NEW NAME: METROPOLITAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Skyline Two, the $45-million apartment complex being built in the South Park 
area in downtown Los Angeles at 950 S. Flower St., has been renamed the 
Metropolitan, according to Dianne Severance, project manager for Forest City 
Properties Corp., the Los Angeles-based developer. 
</P>
<P>
Severance said the new name will give the apartment project, the first in South 
Park, a separate identity from the adjacent Skyline condominiums. They were 
completed in 1983. 
</P>
<P>
Greg Serrao, principal of Dworsky Associates of Los Angeles and the architect 
in charge of the Metropolitan apartments, said the complex "will be like a 
downtown resort -- an oasis complete with palm trees." 
</P>
<P>
The project, he said, is an opportunity to create a pleasant residential 
environment in what had been a neglected light industrial area. 
</P>
