<HEADLINE>
<P>
PLEASED WITH PLAN FOR GLOCKENSPIEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I was delighted to read that there will finally be a glockenspiel in the heart 
of Beverly Hills. (Times, Jan. 9). 
</P>
<P>
It was my pleasure to see the one in Munich a few years ago and watch its 
impact on its surroundings, as well as people. There was an aura of festivity 
in its location in St. Mary's Square, City Hall and a lovely cathedral, with 
outdoor parking slots and tables and chairs where people lounged or ate and 
drank. 
</P>
<P>
And when the glockenspiel was in motion, everyone seemed to communicate with 
smiles and gestures and just plain watching. It was like a pause that 
refreshed, and I would hope that the one in Beverly Hills will serve a similar 
purpose. 
</P>
<P>
SHERRY TERZIAN 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
