<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHOOT-'EM-UPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When are people such as Alex Murashko (Letters, Feb. 5) going to learn that 
real gunplay and reel gunplay are as different as apples and oranges? 
</P>
<P>
I'm sure the producers of "No Retreat, No Surrender II" had no intention of 
bringing to mind the tragic shooting in Stockton. And I'm sure when people go 
to see movies like "No Retreat" or "Rambo," "Commando" and others, the 
tragedies of what they saw on the 6 o'clock news certainly doesn't enter their 
minds. They're going to see a movie, for God's sakes! 
</P>
<P>
What do you suggest the movie makers use instead of firearms? Peashooters? 
</P>
<P>
HOWARD L. MOORE 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, No peashooter. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
