<P>
COSMONAUTS EAT HIGH ON SPACE STATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By from Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MOSCOW 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
What do you feed a hungry cosmonaut? 
</P>
<P>
The Soviet news agency Tass suggests the fare aboard the Mir space station is 
so out-of-this-world that it would bring water to the mouths of earthbound 
gourmets. 
</P>
<P>
"Some dishes are so exquisite that lovers of gourmet food on Earth would be 
glad to have them," the news agency said last week. "These include chicken 
paste with plums, sturgeon with jellied sauce, processed fruit and all kinds of 
juices." 
</P>
