<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST: WALK TO RAISE MONEY FOR HUNGRY; 
</P>
<P>
LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Several hundred harbor area residents will stage a 10-kilometer walk around 
Point Fermin on Saturday to raise money for the hungry. 
</P>
<P>
The ninth annual Los Angeles Harbor Hunger Walk, sponsored by an 
interdenominational group of churches, will begin at 10 a.m. at Point Fermin 
Park. 
</P>
<P>
The walkers have raised as much as $25,000 in previous years. This year 25% of 
their proceeds will go to local charities and the remainder will be distributed 
nationally by the Church World Service, which sponsors similar walks across the 
country. 
</P>
<P>
Those interested in joining the walk may contact Duane Eberhardt at 831-1105 or 
Cindy Murry at 831-6736. 
</P>
</TEXT>
