<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRESIDENT BUSH ON GUN CONTROL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Having been on the receiving end of many AK-47 assault rifles some 20 years ago 
as a combat infantry soldier in South Vietnam, the ongoing controversy 
surrounding these weapons amazes and appalls me, especially the reported 
dramatic rise in sales of these tools of war in the face of pending regulation 
(Part I, Feb. 11). 
</P>
<P>
I cannot help but wonder what is wrong with this civilization (and I use the 
term loosely), in which some members hold a perverse fascination with a weapon 
that was used to kill a good number of the 58,000 Americans who lost their 
lives in Vietnam. 
</P>
<P>
I wonder how many citizens of Vietnam have the same fascination with our AR-15 
(M-16) rifle and are scurrying around their country in a similar buying frenzy. 
Anybody want to guess? 
</P>
<P>
JAMES N. WHITE 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Beach 
</P>
