RIO MESA'S COOK WINS MASTERS TITLE IN 132-POUND CLASS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Robby Cook of Rio Mesa High defeated Mike Verbeck of Savanna, 5-3, to win the 
132-pound weight class at the Southern Section Masters wrestling tournament 
Saturday at Fountain Valley High. 
</P>
<P>
Cook, the lone winner from the Valley area, qualified for the state 
championships March 3-4 at University of the Pacific in Stockton. The top six 
finishers in each weight class qualified for the state finals. 
</P>
<P>
Other top finishers among Valley-area wrestlers included Chris Kilbane of 
Newbury Park, who placed second in the 154-pound class after losing in the 
final to Chris Mollkoy of Katella, 7-4. Billy Hunter of Westlake finished 
second at 175 pounds after losing in the final, 5-2, to Joe Pastorella of 
Katella. 
</P>
<P>
T. R. Merickel of Channel Islands placed third at 126 pounds with a 5-3 
decision over Pat Kinney of El Dorado. Tony Flores of Rio Mesa finished third 
at 191 pounds with a 9-5 victory over Justin Davis of Paso Robles. 
