<TEXT>
<P>
A story in The Times last Sunday about a $4.9-million Orange County Superior 
Court settlement in a home spa accident case incorrectly stated that Blue Haven 
Pools and Spas was bankrupt. Actually, the Garden Grove company, which made the 
spa in which a 10-year-old boy was paralyzed when he was sucked to the bottom, 
is now out of business and was not a party to the settlement. The company was 
sold in 1984 to Earl Dexter Corp., which now operates the business as Blue 
Haven Pools and Spas of Orange County. 
</P>
</TEXT>
