<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFING: EVENTS IN THE NEWS THIS WEEK. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The premier of British Columbia, William N. Vander Zalm, will speak Thursday at 
the opening of the British Columbia Trade and Tourism Office in Irvine, the 
first foreign trade office in Orange County. Also attending will be John 
Jansen, the province's minister of international business and immigration, and 
Bill Reid, minister of tourism and provincial secretary. 
</P>
<P>
California is British Columbia's third largest trading partner, trailing Japan 
and the Pacific Northwest. The office is being opened to further encourage 
collaboration between British Columbia and California in the form of increased 
trade, investment and tourism, officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA022689-0233 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 24133 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
February 26, 1989, Sunday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
