<HEADLINE>
<P>
LEWIS DISMISSED FROM FULLERTON'S BASKETBALL TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rashone Lewis was dismissed from the Cal State Fullerton basketball team 
Saturday by Athletic Director Ed Carroll for violating a university regulation, 
the school announced in a press release. 
</P>
<P>
"I discussed the situation with Coach John Sneed and he concurred with the 
decision," Carroll said. 
</P>
<P>
Carroll would not elaborate on the offense, but said that it would be up to 
Sneed whether Lewis could return next season. 
</P>
<P>
Sneed said it was a "possibility." 
</P>
<P>
Lewis, a 6-foot-5 sophomore forward, played in all 24 games as a reserve. He 
was averaging 1.3 points and two rebounds a game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
DISMISSALS; CALIFORNIA STATE UNIVERSITY AT FULLERTON; COLLEGE ATHLETICS; 
BASKETBALL PLAYERS 
</P>
